43 State Forester shall in no other way be subject to or receive
44 benefits of the state Merit System. Until otherwise provided
45 for by the commission, the present State Forester of the
46 Division of Forestry of the Department of Conservation and
47 Natural Resources shall continue to serve as the State
48 Forester under the commission. The State Forester shall devote
49 his or her full time to the duties of histhe office. He or she
50 shall be required to take the oath of office and give bond in
51 the sum of fifty thousand dollars ($50,000).00."
